job_title: Data Analyst - Reporting & Analytics - Recruitment Services
summary:
The Recruitment Services Data Analyst for Reporting & Analytics is responsible for the execution and rollout of key performance metrics (KPIs), standardized reporting, dashboards and ad hoc reports that support HR/Recruiting leadership by providing timely information and answers to key business questions needed to drive the business forward. The role of the Data Analyst is to turn data into information, and information into insight. It is also integral to informing our stakeholders with meaningful metrics, and visualizations. This role also informs enhancements to various recruiting data management systems and tools to drive continual improvement of the data integrity.

This role is responsible to scale the recruitment reporting strategy across the globe, taking into consideration the nuances of the different regions and teams. This includes translating requirements from various stakeholders, interpreting data, analyzing results using statistical techniques, as well as providing feedback to measure impact and effectiveness of the messaging. Specifically, this includes creating, managing and maintaining a prioritization process, support queue, various project plans, schedules, deliverables and status reports. This role is integral to helping shape, implement and drive quality reports, dashboards, metrics and enhanced data integrity that ultimately tells the recruitment story.

The person we seek will join a team of technology, operations and recruiting professionals who work with the worldwide recruiting organization to deliver recruitment reporting solutions. This role will also work collaboratively with the HR Analytics team. This person must be resourceful, adaptable, creative, and results oriented with high energy and a positive attitude.

Key Qualifications
Proven ability to proactively establish rapport, credibility and influence, and drive results throughout an organization at all levels.
Technical expertise regarding data models, database design development, data mining and segmentation techniques.
Strong knowledge of and experience with reporting packages (Business Objects, Tableau, etc.), databases (SQL etc), programming (XML, Javascript, or ETL frameworks)
Knowledge of statistics and experience using statistical packages for analyzing large datasets (Excel, SPSS, SAS etc)
Strong analytical skills with the ability to collect, organize, analyze, and disseminate significant amounts of information with attention to detail and accuracy.
Adept at queries, report writing and presenting findings.
Knowledge of recruiting processes and workflows and be able to support, understand, and enhance the data integrity of our systems.
Must have superlative written and verbal skills as well as strong presentation skills.
Must be able to balance working in a creatively driven organization, with an analytical and disciplined approach to technology and ability to present solutions in a simple, understandable language to client groups.
Uses proven concepts and company objectives to resolve complex issues in creative and effective ways.
Organized, able to provide clear direction for others to understand easily.

Description
Develop and implement data collection systems and other strategies that optimize statistical efficiency and data quality.
Acquire data from primary or secondary data sources and maintain databases/data systems.
Identify, analyze, and interpret trends or patterns in complex data sets.
Filter and clean data, and review computer reports, printouts, and performance indicators to locate and correct code problems.
Work closely with management to prioritize business and information needs.
Locate and define new process improvement opportunities.
Manage and deliver projects and change initiatives, including educating the teams on metrics, reports, system usage and support.
Have a point of view and the ability to influence others to meet the needs of the business operational insights to the Recruiting Leadership Team through analytics and reporting that allow them to make decisions on where and how to use our resources.
Connect and provide context and content that becomes the means to train and continuously improve the efficiency and effectivity of Recruiting to deliver.
Create Project Plans and a Master Schedule that predicts delivery dates based on an objective analysis.
Work on complex issues where analysis of situations or data requires and in-depth evaluation of variable factors.
Exercise judgment in influencing methods, techniques and evaluation criteria for obtaining results.
Respond to inquiries quickly and support accurate communications about solutions.

Education
Bachelor's degree or equivalent is preferred. Focus in Mathematics, Economics, Computer Science, or Information Management a plus.
3 + years of data analysis and reporting experience. Recruitment services, operations or related project management experience a plus.

Additional Requirements
Consult & Evolve
Able to leverage subject matter expertise to create flexible solutions to real business needs.
Build a strong understanding of the recruitment organization and processes you support, build relationships and earn credibility.
Manage and deliver business KPIs, reporting and analytics are relevant and tell the story to our stakeholders.
Possess strong process orientation with an innate curiosity to drive continual improvement and data integrity.
Proactively research, develop and adopt competitive and innovative recruitment reporting and analytic practices.

Collaborate & Influence
Exercise diplomacy and perseverance.
Able to gather the right resources to create business solutions.
Create productive and collaborative partnerships with all key stakeholders.
Gather, analyze and synthesize information to make holistic recommendations.
Over-communicate plans, progress and wins, yet able to flex and reset based on feedback.

Drive & Deliver
Self-starter, who takes initiative, owns decisions, and is calm in the face of pressure.
Willing to get into the details to solve problems & create solutions.
Able to demonstrate flexibility, research & investigate multiple options for consideration.
Able to juggle competing priorities and drive timely execution of projects.
Tenacious in designing elegant solutions that will scale and improve insight, efficiency, productivity, and consistency.

job_title: Internal Data Tools, Business Intelligence Analyst
summary:
Apple is seeking a proven Business Intelligence Analyst to join the Internal Data Tools team. Youll partner with other business analysts and internal stakeholders to understand reporting requirements, work closely with data engineers to design supporting data models, and deliver dashboards using our internal data reporting platform. You will need to understand how to curate and communicate complex data in a clear dashboard view, often partnering with UI engineers to build new compelling visualizations. As part of a centralized team that supports marketing, operations, product management, engineering, business - amongst other teams - youll act as a thought partner and domain expert on data and help in driving decision making at Apple. This is a full-time position in Apple Media Products and is located in our Cupertino, CA office.

Key Qualifications
2-5 years of industry experience in a Business Intelligence role
Well-versed in SQL languages. Experience with big data frameworks preferred
Well-versed with data visualization and building dashboards, e.g. Tableau or similar
Knowledge of data modeling and database schema design
Excellent communication skills, both written and oral
Excellent project management skills
Description
Wireframe, prototype and build dashboards to support informed decision making on key business initiatives
Partner with reporting analysts and data engineers to design and build supporting data models
Contribute towards centralized documentation
Organize QA and UAT
Define success metrics for projects and review post-launch

Education
Minimum of a Bachelors degree in Economics, Computer Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering or relevant field. Ideally, Masters in related field.

Overview As a Business Intelligence Analyst/Developer, you will play a key role in developing and maintaining BI solutions within the organization. You will develop reports, dashboards, scorecards, and other data products using DOMO, Excel and other tools. You will work with cross functional teams to ensure training, performance and reliability of data. The ideal candidate will have experience with the DOMO BI platform or similar platforms (Tableau, Looker, Birst, etc.), with the ability to translate complex business requirements into actionable reporting tools for internal and client use. You will be responsible for gathering and interpreting data on call center trends. You will analyze agent population metrics such as attrition, performance, and behaviors, as well as call center performance including call handling and client performance. You must be a self-starter who loves digging into data and discovering insights hidden within that data.

Responsibilities
Play a critical role in the design, development, support, and continuous improvement of the BI environment supporting internal and external stakeholders
Analyze complex data from multiple sources, determining configuration and connection methods for ingestion by BI tool
Develop BI solutions according to user requirements, best practices, and industry standards.
Participate/lead in a full BI development lifecycle including planning, architecture design, development, testing, migration, and production support
Develop and enhance ETL processes for performance and scalability handling data from multiple sources
Identifies, researches, and resolves technical problems with dashboards, reports, and source data
Analyze call center trends and provide recommendations for improvements
Run A/B tests to optimize client and agent performance
Discover correlations between agent behaviors and performance metrics
Work collaboratively to interface with and understand analytical reporting needs of business stakeholders
Effectively communicate (written and verbal) technical subject matter to non-technical business stakeholders, be a source of training and insight on the DOMO platform to facilitate knowledge transfer and value recognition of BI
Implement data hygiene controls and ensure data integrity and accuracy
Work with disparate data sources and systems to facilitate a mature BI environment

Qualifications
Bachelors Degree in a quantitative or technical field
Demonstrated proficiency in general database administration concepts
Displays an eagerness to continually improve their skills and learn new technologies
Excellence with at least one BI tool (DOMO, Tableau, Looker, etc.). Experience or proficiency in DOMO preferred
Strong understanding of SQL; able to write complex queries
Comfortable with - and able to consume and construct - APIs
Experience with data design and development including data modeling, mapping data elements from various data sources and loading objects including dimensions, hierarchies, tables, and aggregates
Experience in full-stack development of front-end and back-end technology; skill and experience constructing the underlying data layer supporting a BI launch, with skill and experience on the front-end developing report, dashboards, and visualizations
Advanced data analysis skills (proficient in Excel, data manipulation and data set creation)
Ability to work autonomously but also in collaboration with cross functional teams
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills
Thrive in a fast-paced environment with tight deadlines
Excellent written and oral communication skills
Workers in this position will be in a general office environment and required to sit, stand, walk, bend, stoop and lift to 50 pounds while operating office equipment and conducting daily duties.

Many businesses are data driven, but perhaps none so much as Microsoft. A great deal of effort is spent on using masses of data to understand user behavior to inform and improve upon Microsofts products and marketing efforts.

With petabytes of data being collected, we enable data driven decisions by converting data into insights that drive enhanced customer experiences and improve business performance.

The ideal candidate should be self-directed, passionate about data, and focused on delivering the right results. The candidate should be able to apply programming acumen and a breadth of tools, data sources and analytical techniques to answer a wide range of high-impact business questions and present the insights in a concise and effective manner. Technical aptitude and programming skills are necessary in this role. The candidate should also be an effective communicator capable of independently driving issues to resolution and communicating insights to both technical and non-technical audiences.

Core Responsibilities:
Build a holistic understanding of our product features, its customer, the BI data infrastructure & environment, and business goals
Develop powerful visualization on customer behavior and usage and become SMEs for the product(s)

Leverage industry best practices in establishing repeatable BI practices, principles & processes
Leverage team members across BI, for data & analysis needs
Refine, improve and centralize team capabilities and share to the broader business and analytical community
Manage external vendor relationships onshore & offshore, as needed Key Skills, Competencies.
Qualifications:
Unique mix of technical, development, project and program management skills
Ability to understand, translate and map business and product questions into analysis projects
Expertise in database technology with solid understanding and hands-on skills with SQL Server, SSIS, solid understanding of SSAS / n-dimensional cubes
Solid experience building business intelligence solutions (data warehouse, ETL, Reports, Powerpivots) and ability to understand instrumentation and devise technical solutions
Proficiency in advanced Excel functions (e.g., creating formulas, pivot tables) and PowerBI
Knowledge of SAS, SPSS, Tableau, Adobe Insights or similar analytic software
Ability to influence diverse audiences and build strong partnerships with stakeholders

Self-motivated, agile and driven to think out-of-the-box
3+ years of data analysis experience required; College degree required, MSc/MA/MBA preferred

You will also be introducing data science capabilities into the Customer Support function and come up with new innovative predictive and actionable use cases to create business value with the help of the data. You will have the opportunity to collaborate with our internal data science community to share knowledge and best practices from different business functions.

summary:
Position Description
Position: Analyst III, Business Intelligence and Reporting

Job Location: Bentonville, AR

Duties: Develops complex business intelligence and reporting solutions by identifying business requirements; researching potential solutions; making recommendations to meet end user business objectives; conducting analysis and design; creating visual prototypes and design documentation; writing detailed dashboard and reporting specifications; and creating reports and visualization of information to effectively communication results. Leads projects to completion by working with project stakeholders to ensure alignment on project strategy and results; assisting in the resolution of team conflicts; developing written and oral presentations for diverse audiences (for example, management, customers, suppliers, business intelligence and analytics staff); teaching reporting technologies through informal and formal mentorship both inside and outside the team; providing subject matter expertise for reporting projects; driving projects to completion; and communicating project results and updates to senior leadership. Develops business intelligence solution roadmaps by gathering required information; working with subject matter experts in appropriate business areas; documenting and revising processes to collect, analyze, compile and submit reportable information to federal, state and local government agencies; collaborating with data experts and other business intelligence and analytics experts; coordinating the evaluation of customer and supplier solutions; and presenting application solutions to diverse audiences (for example, analytics associates, business customers). Develops business intelligence solutions with customers and other system areas by ensuring testing and validation; overseeing upgrades and release schedules for business intelligence and database products; managing production of scheduled regulatory reports; ensuring requirements are met to support implementations; managing compliance reporting database to ensure accuracy and completeness of the data; ensuring development of system documentation; developing materials for state of the art user interfaces that enable the business users to interpret trends and exceptions; and reviewing change implementation before and after production installations.

Minimum Qualifications
Minimum education and experience required: Bachelors degree or equivalent in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business, or related field and 2 years experience in an Information Technology, Business or related role. In lieu of a Bachelors degree and 2 years experience, employer will accept 4 years experience in an Information Technology, Business or related role.

Skills required: Must have experience with: data collection, gathering, mapping, extraction and transformation; descriptive and exploratory analysis, including mean, standard deviation, and regression; designing and developing KPI in reporting; inferential statistics, including time series, correlation, association, and clustering; data analysis and mining using SQL; regulatory compliance for retail organization, including factory audit, food safety and business ethics; business requirements gathering and documentation; business process documentation, analysis, redesign and optimization; quality assurance testing; and R and Python to retrieve, merge, and hygiene data from multiple sources. Employer will accept any amount of professional experience in the required skills.

Additional Preferred Qualifications

Transform the way business users consume data and insights through well-designed dashboards and self-service modules
Be a strategic partner and influencer with wide cross functional team of business users and engineers

5+ years of relevant experience in either Data Warehouse Engineering or Business Intelligence, ideally in a consumer facing data driven organization

Individuals within the Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst role identify business intelligence, reporting, and data analysis needs. You will work closely with clients and IT teams to turn data into critical information and knowledge that can be used to make sound business decisions. It is essential that BI Analysts build an understanding of the business at a level of detail that enables them to identify and address critical issues. You must provide data that is accurate, congruent and reliable, and ensure the information is easily available to users for direct consumption or integration with other systems. BI Analysts educate and train clients to use the data as an analytical tool, displaying the information in new forms and content for the purpose of analysis and option exploration.
BI Analysts work with clients to determine business requirements, priorities, define key performance indicators (KPI), and develop BI and data warehouse (DW) strategy. This includes working with business and development teams to design, and document dashboards, alerts, and reports. This individual is accountable for providing leadership and independent initiatives in facilitating information gathering, structured documentation and presentation of findings to all levels of management. They conduct analyses of functional business processes and functional business requirements and participate in the development of business cases in the support of process changes and/or IT projects.
BI Analysts understand how data is turned into information and knowledge and how that knowledge supports and enables key business processes. They must have an in-depth understanding of the business environment and an interest in going beyond the obvious, delving into the source, the definition, philosophy, and foundational roots of a data element in order to create information. They must work well within a team environment.

summary:
Summary: The Operations Analysis & Performance (OAP) team at Delta provides database reporting and analytical support across all major operations areas of the company. OAP's newly formed decision science team seeks a data engineering analytics leader to take on developing data-driven solutions aimed at continually improving airline performance and decision making.

The ideal candidate will have deep technical knowledge of BI systems design, big data architecture and technology landscape, api consumption, ETL/ELT orchestration, and business intelligence tools. The candidate should have excellent organizational and communication skills and be able to work effectively in a fast-paced environment. 2. Manage administration, configuration, monitoring, performance, maintenance and usability of BI systems. This duty is performed as needed, about 5% of the time.

3. Develop, maintain and manage metadata, reporting, analytics, dashboards, report definitions, data extracts, etc. Designs, codes, tests and document all new or existing BI solutions. Writing complex queries, views and stored procedures. This duty is performed daily, about 10% of the time.

4. Solve complex data issue using data analyst skills to determine root cause problem for data integrity and data quality issues. This duty is performed as needed, about 5% of the time.

5. Collaborate with departments to identify and scope the business opportunity, to understand, document and analyze business requirements, identify effective reporting techniques, the best data sources, risks and constraints, and desired reporting formats that drive the development and design of BI solution. This duty is performed daily, about 20% of the time.

Individuals within the Business Intelligence (BI) Analyst role identify business intelligence, reporting, and data analysis needs. You will work closely with clients and IT teams to turn data into critical information and knowledge that can be used to make sound business decisions. It is essential that BI Analysts build an understanding of the business at a level of detail that enables them to identify and address critical issues. You must provide data that is accurate, congruent and reliable, and ensure the information is easily available to users for direct consumption or integration with other systems. BI Analysts educate and train clients to use the data as an analytical tool, displaying the information in new forms and content for the purpose of analysis and option exploration.

BI Analysts work with clients to determine business requirements, priorities, define key performance indicators (KPI), and develop BI and data warehouse (DW) strategy. This includes working with business and development teams to design, and document dashboards, alerts, and reports. This individual is accountable for providing leadership and independent initiatives in facilitating information gathering, structured documentation and presentation of findings to all levels of management. They conduct analyses of functional business processes and functional business requirements and participate in the development of business cases in the support of process changes and/or IT projects.

BI Analysts understand how data is turned into information and knowledge and how that knowledge supports and enables key business processes. They must have an in-depth understanding of the business environment and an interest in going beyond the obvious, delving into the source, the definition, philosophy, and foundational roots of a data element in order to create information. They must work well within a team environment.

As a BI Developer at Indeed, your role is to be an expert at understanding Indeed's data. We expect you to aid our business teams in drawing insight from our data. Learning from, and sharing knowledge and skills with your teammates to grow BIs total impact to the organization.

job_title: HBO Vice President, Data Engineering Services
summary:
OVERALL SUMMARY

The Vice President, Data Engineering Services (DES) within the Media Technology & Information Services (MTIS) group is responsible for the leadership and architecture of our Data and Analytics platform ecosystem.

As a senior leader in Technology this position will work extensively with HBO executive management, business unit representatives, data stewards, and technology stakeholders to define, implement and sustain our Data & Analytics platform (DAP) & Business Intelligence (BI) solutions which support all of HBOs platforms and business areas.

This position is responsible for defining and implementing data integration architecture, enterprise reference data, and data quality solutions across HBO and includes the assessment of new and existing platform architecture frameworks, software & hardware technologies, as well as the evaluation and selection on premise and cloud technologies.

The VP, Data Engineering Services will lead a team of engineering managers, software engineers and consultants (on and offshore) assigned to software development and technical architecture teams that support enterprise wide applications and tools to drive the down stream media supply chain systems as well as the data and analytics solutions used to market, measure and retain HBO subscribers. Transforming the technical management of data to drive the growth and evolve the customer experience is a primary goal of this position.

We are looking for a passionate, high energy individual who is excited about delivering data driven capabilities to meet HBOs growing insights, analytics and intelligence capabilities leveraging the best in class industry proven solutions. This individual must have a track record of working in a highly collaborative environment and should take pride in evolving the entire organization to create the future data technology platform for HBOs growth. This position will be based in New York City and report to the Senior Vice President Media Technology & Information Services.

Primary Responsibilities:
Lead strategy, architecture and the development of data and analytics solutions.
Collaborate with peers in Research, Marketing, Distribution, Finance, and Technology to prioritize, plan and release capabilities within the Data and Analytics platform ecosystem.
Develop, mentor and manage a team of technical leaders, engineers and architects.

Lead a team that supports the data platform, applications and workflows 24x7.
Ability to lead teams using different delivery and execution models and sheperd agile practices and processes.

Innovate with and expand the organization's insight, intelligence and analytics offerings, emerging approaches, skills and technologies.
Research and develop new data solutions and tools sets.

Have you ever thought about what it takes to detect and prevent fraudulent activity among hundreds of millions of eCommerce transactions across the globe? What would you do to increase trust in an online marketplace where millions of buyers and sellers transact? How would you build systems that evolve over time to proactively identify and neutralize new and emerging fraud threats?

Our mission in Transaction Risk Management Services (TRMS) is to make Amazon.com the safest place to transact online. TRMS safeguards every financial transaction across all Amazon sites, while striving to ensure that these efforts are transparent to our legitimate customers. As such, TRMS designs and builds the software systems, risk models and operational processes that minimize risk and maximize trust in Amazon.com.

As a Business Analyst in TRMS, you will be responsible for analyzing terabytes of data to identify specific instances of risk, broader risk trends and points of customer friction, developing scalable solutions for prevention. You will work with team members to ensure that the volume being flagged for manual review aligns with available capacity and Service Level Agreements (SLAs) are met. In addition you will be responsible for building a robust set of operational and business metrics and will utilize metrics to determine improvement opportunities.

Responsibilities :
Understand the various operations across TRMS
Understand the requirements of stakeholders and map them with the data sources/data warehouse
Design and develop highly available dashboards and metrics using SQL and Tableau.
Provide wing-to-wing project lifecycle execution (project planning, execution, risk assessment and system availability)
Execute high priority (i.e. cross functional, high impact) projects to improve operations performance with the help of Operations Analytics managers
Perform business analysis and data queries using SAS/R
Execute analytical projects and understanding of analytical methods (like ANOVA, Distribution theory, regression, forecasting, Machine Learning Techniques, etc.)
Develop and oversee the initiation of strategy recommendations
Use statistical analysis to segment customer behavior and develop targeted solutions to prevent deposit and debit card fraud

At least 3-5 years of experience working in Analytics / Business Intelligence environment
Experience in working with databases and SQL in a business environment
Demonstrated use of analytical packages and query languages such as SAS,SPSS and SQL
Prior experience in design and execution of analytical projects
Worked extensively in large scale data bases and data warehouses
Previous experience deploying Machine Learning-based Risk algorithms

Experience in e-commerce / on-line companies in fraud / risk control functions
Graduate Degree preferred
Exposure to software development process
Analytical mindset and ability to see the big picture and influence others

Strong oral, written and presentation skills combined with the ability to lead group discussions and explaining complex solutions

We are currently seeking a Product Owner who takes ownership of a digital platform sub system. Specifically, the PO will lead the Agile team through the progressive elaboration process which includes the technical scope, estimation, backlog grooming, sprint planning and sprint execution steps. Responsible for acting as a liaison between key stakeholders.

Principal Responsibilities/Objectives:

1. Progressive Elaboration
In collaboration with a Principal Software Engineer (PSE), the PO is responsible for defining the EPIC into user and tech stories including dataflow diagrams and use cases (Technical Scope). They are responsible for task breakdown, story execution strategy, accepting stories, representing the customer to the Agile team and coordination of content dependencies with other Product Owners (Sprint Planning).

Works closely with the PSE, Scrum Master & the Agile team to ensure the actual build is going according to plan. The Product Owner is responsible for story clarification, escalation and decision making. The PO participates in the daily standups and ensures the Agile teams activities and velocity are properly recorded on the Jira platform to ensure consistency with the objectives of the project.

Owns production support issues including research to eliminate bugs. Prioritizes bugs within the backlog and crushes high priority bugs within service level agreement timelines.

The People Analytics team acts as an internal innovation lab, using analytical approaches to make sure Google continues to be a great place to work. summary:
Company Overview

At Proofpoint, we have a passion for protecting people, data, and brands from todays advanced threats and compliance risks. We hire the best people in the business to:

The Role

The Business Intelligence/Data Engineer role is an engineering-focused position, focused on creating a managed flow of data from our product sources to effectively answer questions for Engineering, Product Management, Marketing, Sales, Finance and Operations. Your work will take the operational, usage and behavioral metrics from our products and cloud services, integrate that data with our internal business metrics and be able to provide visualization and answer questions about how the business is doing.

Create the data source interfaces between our product data sources and the data stores/warehouse
Work with Engineering to gather, understand and stream the disparate data sources

Conduct ad-hoc analysis and reviews to identify efficiency and cost-improvements across the business

Experience in Data Warehousing: MSSQL 2012 or 2016, MySQL Data Warehouse, IBM InfoSphere, etc.

Expertise with Data exploration techniques: SQL, Hive, etc.
Familiarity with Business Analytics tools: Pendo, Pentaho, Birst, etc.
Familiarity with Data visualization tools: Tableau, PowerBI, etc.
Familiarity with Machine Learning (a plus)
Familiarity with Salesforce (a plus)
3+ years of experience in a business analytics/intelligence/data warehousing job
Excellent communication skills (written and spoken)

POSITION DESCRIPTION:

The Director of Business Intelligence will lead data warehousing, information delivery and analytic functions for the organization. This position will build and operate data, reporting and analytic infrastructure that enables the organization to achieve its goals by facilitating the flow of timely, high quality information.

ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS:

1. Primary responsibility for data, reporting and analytical capabilities for organization.

2. Conducts detailed assessment of organization's data, reporting and analytic needs.

3. Develops multi-year data, reporting and analytics strategy and roadmap and gains approval from executive leadership.

4. Builds out, organizes and appropriately staffs the business intelligence team to meet the needs of the organization.

5. Leads design and development of data warehouse.

6. Oversees development of cascading scorecards, dashboards and other performance reporting tools.

7. Serves as an expert consultant to senior leaders and operational leaders in the development and implementation of analytic methods, performance metrics and reports needed to achieve organizational goals.

8. Partners with VP, IT to select and implement reporting and analytic tools.

ORGANIZATIONAL EXPECTATIONS:

1. Creates a positive, professional, service-oriented work environment for staff, patients and family members by supporting the IHA CARES mission and core values statement.

2. Must be able to work effectively as a member of the Planning & Development team.

3. Successfully completes IHA's "The Customer" training and adheres to IHA's standard of promptly providing a high level of service and respect to internal or external customers.

4. Maintains knowledge of and complies with IHA standards, policies and procedures, including IHA's Employee Handbook.

5. Maintains complete knowledge of office services and in the use of all relevant office equipment, computer, and manual systems.

6. Maintains strict patient and employee confidentiality in compliance with IHA and HIPAA guidelines

7. Serves as a role model, by demonstrating exceptional ability and willingness to take on new and additional responsibilities. Embraces new ideas and respect cultural differences.

8. Uses resources efficiently.

9. If applicable, responsible for ongoing professional development  maintains appropriate licensure/certification and continuing education credentials, participates in available learning opportunities.

MEASURED BY:

Performance that meets or exceeds IHA CARES Values expectation as outlined in IHA Performance Review document, relative to position.

ESSENTIAL QUALIFICATIONS:

EDUCATION: Bachelor's degree required. Master's degree in system science, business administration, statistics, economics, computer science, healthcare administration, public health, health policy and management or other quantitative field preferred.

CREDENTIALS/LICENSURE: None

MINIMUM EXPERIENCE: Minimum seven (7) years in the health care industry, preferably in data management or health economics. Minimum five (5) years as a manager of data management and analytical staff.

POSITION REQUIREMENTS (ABILITIES & SKILLS):

1. Strong technical knowledge of BI and reporting concepts, such as data warehouses, data modeling, ETL, SQL and reporting tools. SSRS knowledge preferred but not required.

2. Statistics foundation with working knowledge of control charts, statistical significance and study design.

3. Excellent project management, communication and analytical skills.

4. Customer-focus mindset that emphasizes role as supporting patient care.

5. Ability to foster teamwork and build a strong culture of collaboration.

6. Ability to work effectively and develop good working relationships with various levels of organizational members and diverse populations including IHA staff, management, providers, provider and executive leadership, patients and family members, insurance carriers, vendors, SJMHS and Trinity Health.

7. Ability to handle patient and organizational information in a confidential manner.

MINIMUM PHYSICAL EXPECTATIONS:

1. Physical activity that often requires keyboarding, filing and phone work.

2. Physical activity that often requires extensive time working on a computer.

3. Physical activity that sometimes requires walking, standing, bending, stooping, reaching, and/or twisting.

4. Physical activity that sometimes requires lifting, pushing and/or pulling under 30 lbs.

5. Specific vision abilities required include close vision, depth perception, peripheral vision and the ability to adjust and focus.

6. Manual dexterity sufficient to operate a keyboard, photocopier, telephone, calculator and other office equipment.

7. Requires the ability to drive to other office sites.

8. Must hear and speak well enough to conduct business over the telephone or face to face for long periods of time in English.

MINIMUM ENVIRONMENTAL EXPECTATIONS:

This job operates in a typical office environment which involves frequent interruptions and significate interaction with people which can be stressful at times.

Description

Job Summary:
The Business Analytics Specialist provides financial and operational analyses to hospital revenue cycle leaders and operational teams to enhance organizational decision-making. The primary purpose is to provide data driven insights and actionable information to drive improvement, efficiency and best practices in hospital revenue cycle.

Job Description:
1. Builds strong consultative relationships, establishing value as a key business partner for information and a data insights advisor to the Business. Translates customer data questions and requirements into actionable analytic score cards, dashboards, reports in support of financial and revenue cycle improvement projects and initiatives. Leads the development of effective key performance indicators, management dashboards and balanced scorecards that provide enhanced insight and improve organizational decision-making.

2. Provides data models that generate operational and strategic insights to inform short- and long-term business objectives. Participates in development of data variables and data dictionaries, using data dictionaries to obtain relevant data elements and build reporting logic to solve complex business problems.

3. Functions as a liaison between project stakeholders and Information Services Division (ISD). Synthesizes information from a variety of internal and external sources to support actionable business decisions. Ensures the highest level of data integrity and security across UNC Health Care's business intelligence portfolio. Drafts reporting requirements and engages ISD development partners to implement solutions as needed. Ensures ad-hoc reporting requests are captured, prioritized and where possible create standardized dynamic reports to meet ad hoc reporting needs. Collaborates with Business Analyst on training and education of end users and team members on self-service reporting tools, including preparation of instructional materials such as PowerPoint presentations, procedure documents and data dictionaries.

Strong analytical and problem solving skills. Experience managing multiple and competing tasks and priorities with delivery deadlines in fast paced, complex environment. summary:
Introduction

1052 IS Business Analyst - Epic Business Intelligence Developer
San Francisco Department of Public Health

The Department of Public Health (DPH) is looking to procure three (3) temporary exempt (up to 3 years) 1052 IS Business Analyst - Epic Business Intelligence Developer positions to help design, develop & implement DPHs unified electronic health record solution.

APPOINTMENT TYPE:
Temporary Exempt (TEX), this position is excluded by the Charter from the competitive Civil Service examination process and shall serve at the discretion of the Appointing Officer.

POSITION DESCRIPTION:
DPHwill be implementing the Epic electronic health record. Under the direction of an IT Epic Program Management Director, the Epic Business Intelligence Developer implements various parts of the systems development cycle, systems analysis, design and build, project planning, system installation, implementation and testing, conversion to production status, technical and procedural documentation, user training support, and post-implementation analysis and support.

The Epic Business Intelligence Team is responsible for designing, testing, and implementing the clinical and financial aspects of the San Francisco Department of Public Health Electronic Health Record. This includes integration and interoperability with other third party clinical and financial systems and devices.

ESSENTIAL DUTIES: The Epic Business Intelligence Developer will be responsible for the following:
 Utilizing knowledge of electronic health records in the hospital, long term and ambulatory care settings to perform tasks.
 Utilizing Epic reporting tools and/or Caboodle data of EPIC electronic Health record and associated integration with various ancillary systems and creates and maintains the analytical database on relational database platform.
 Perform other duties as assigned.

The ideal candidate(s) must have working knowledge in the following:
 Utilize analytical database platform (Microsoft SQL Server) to perform tasks.
 Utilize the analytical database operating system to perform tasks.
 Windows server administration experience or training
 Perform basic troubleshooting on your chosen platform (Microsoft SQL Server), Windows Server, and IIS
 Perform technical analytics and troubleshooting.
 Analyze data, problem solve and clearly communicate solutions

Minimum Qualifications Education:
An associate degree in computer science or a closely related field from an accredited college or university OR its equivalent in terms of total course credits/units [i.e., at least sixty (60) semester or ninety (90) quarter credits/units with a minimum of twenty (20) semester or thirty (30) quarter credits/units in computer science or a closely-related field].

Experience:
One (1) year in the information systems field, including technical support, content management, administration of network applications or system analysis.

One (1) year is equivalent to thirty (30) semester units / forty-five (45) quarter units with a minimum of 10 semester / 15 quarter units in computer science or a closely related field.

Travel to Wisconsin is required to attend Epic training. Appointees will be required to maintain validity of required Epic certification throughout length of employment.

 Proficiency with basic word processing and presentation applications (i.e. MS Office: Word, Excel, PowerPoint). Knowledge of flow diagramming applications and collaboration platforms, SharePoint.

 Technically proficient in your analytical database platform (Microsoft SQL Server)
 Working knowledge of the analytical database operating system
 Windows server administration experience or training
 Ability to perform basic troubleshooting on your chosen platform Microsoft SQL Server, Windows Server, and IIS
 Create and generate reports and statistics to meet user and program requirements; interface with other departments, jurisdictions and users on regulations and reporting requests.

 Skill at tracking tasks, defining next steps, identifying owners and holding people accountable

 Change control and conversion to production status,
 Application services procedural documentation
 Application module optimization in conjunction with stakeholders.

The role:

Santa Clara, CA

Business Introduction:
With the mission of capturing the biggest market share in the area of cyber security, network security, endpoint security, threat research, malware research, cloud security, we work together for a common goal of shaping the companys future by designing and building the best in class robust and scalable security products for consumer and enterprise customers. This is where you come in. We are looking for a new team member who defined by his/her unique and innovative skills, style or point of view. You can be an architect, scientist, threat researcher, developer or may other roles we have at McAfee, as long as you are passionate about things that matters.

As a Data Analyst a typical day might include following:
Helping to understand and optimize business performance across McAfee Mobile and ISP business segments. Through Data mining, predictive modeling, customer segmentation and forecasting, the data analyst will focus on supporting multiple teams and must be committed to answering questions that help us build the best products and develop best practices in marketing, user experience and communication. The Data analyst will also develop high-quality models to gain deeper insights into how people interact with the digital world and specifically McAfee products.

Qualifications

Key Responsibilities:
Act independently to identify and evangelize opportunities for improved analysis and efficiency through better data and analytics practices.
Work closely with business and engineering teams to encourage statistical best practices with respect to experimental design, data capture and data analysis.
Develop and demonstrate improved analysis methodologies and educate stakeholders throughout the company.
Support the optimization of sales and marketing efforts via data mining, modeling, user segmentation and forecasting.
You have:
4+ years of experience in a relevant role

6. Provides expertise in the data structures of one or more types of systems and software such as GE Centricity Business, All scripts, PeopleSoft HCM, FMS or Campus Solutions.
7. Coordinates with IT management, systems analysts, users and other IS technical providers to ensure that client requirements are accomplished.
8. Performs other duties as assigned.

 Experience with computer hardware, software and programming
 Excellent technical and general communication skills, both oral and written
 Certifications in relevant areas such as Oracle, SQL, and Microsoft are highly desirable.
 Clinical or ERP data warehouse implementation and support experience is highly desirable.
 Preferable for candidate to have 2+ years experience in Crystal, SQL (MS SQL Server and/or Oracle), Excel, adhoc and operational reporting, financial and/or clinical business applications.

Minimum Education:

Bachelors degree in computer science, business, or related discipline or related experience in lieu of education.

Minimum Experience:

Two years of relevant experience

Exerts up to 50 pounds of force occasionally and/or up to 20 pounds frequently and/or up to 10 pounds constantly to move objects.

Security Sensitive:

This job class may contain positions that are security sensitive and thereby subject to the provisions of Texas Education Code  51.215.

SUMMARY

Identifies and monitors current and potential customers, using business intelligence tools; seeks and provides information to help the Club determine their position in the marketplace. Collects and synthesizes business intelligence data from internal sources, available industry reports, public information, field reports, or purchased sources, along with trend data to support recommendations for action.

ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES includes the following. Other duties may be assigned.

Queries, extracts and analyzes data from multiple data sources and applies information analysis (i.e. managing large amounts of data and conducting exploratory data analysis) to generate solutions and think conceptually, then synthesizes data to generate meaningful information and to provide actionable insights. Data-savvy, critical thinker with strong attention to detail and high quality standards that ensures the reporting of high-quality metrics data by troubleshooting issues and working with data owners to improve the timeliness and quality of their data.

Prepares reports of findings, illustrating data graphically and translating complex findings into written text. Gathers data on competitors and analyzes their prices, sales, and methods of marketing and distribution. Manages timely flow of business intelligence information to users. Acts as data steward for the business line, acting as primary liaison with the data warehouse team.

Functions independently throughout the lifecycle of a project, adapting as projects evolve, responsible for multiple simultaneous projects. Must be proficient at translating business needs to technical requirements, developing a work plan and reporting progress and risks. Drives business outcomes by gathering and analyzing business data, modeling current and future state of business systems and processes, and converting business data into appropriate metrics and dashboards using data mining, data modeling and analytic tools. Provides end-to-end analytic support including pulling data, preparing analysis, interpreting data, making strategic recommendations and presenting to the internal client.

Designs statistically valid tests of efforts to include appropriate sampling, test/control designs and response tracking by utilizing spreadsheet, database, and statistical software to enter, retrieve and analyze data and perform math functions and basic statistical analysis such as trend analysis, variance, correlation analysis and t-tests. Provides ongoing analytical expertise in the overall business evaluation process and support for special projects that require departmental and Club-wide interaction.

Shares expertise with others, mentors and continually strives to improve overall contributions to the department. Adheres to department policies and procedures regarding confidentiality of information.

QUALIFICATIONS

Bachelors degree in Business Administration, Marketing, Applied Mathematics, Economics ore related field required.
Masters degree in Business, or related field of study preferred.
5 plus years of professional experience in business, marketing or comparable analytics position which includes developing and implementing reporting tools.
5 plus years insurance industry experience.
Knowledge of SQL, Data Analysis, Data Warehousing preferred
Advanced experience in data access and manipulation with SAS as well as retrieving data from large databases with SQL.
Strong leadership, attention to detail, verbal and written communication skills and ability to work well with others in a team environment
Ability to clearly explain technical and analytical information (verbally, written and in presentation format) and apply/summarize for business use including the ability to communicate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.
Excellent organizational skills, multi-tasking and project management are required, including the ability to manage multiple competing priorities with strong attention to detail, accuracy and accountability.
Comfort working with various tools and technologies, including relational database (SQL), BI (SSRS, Tableau), statistical (SPSS, R), web analytics (SiteCatalyst, Google Analytics), and CRM (SalesForce, ExacTarget) software a plus.
Ability to adapt to changing priorities and conditions

This is an Enterprise Operations position supporting the Ethics and Internal Audit organization. The position performs audits across Lockheed Martin (LM) Programs, as a member of the LM Corporate Internal Audit (LMCIA) programs focus group. This role will proactively monitor and report on risks, exposures, internal controls and key performance indicators across various areas of the company. The candidate selected to fill this role will be a member of the Business Leadership Program (BLP). This program offers a unique opportunity to acquire a broad range of skills and experience and gain exposure to many Lockheed Martin businesses, programs, and management through audit assignments.

BLP is a two year program that includes key milestones required for graduation. Each participant will be assigned to an audit team, conduct audits in multiple Business Areas, participate in training and complete a capstone project addressing a senior executive management issue or concern.

This position is virtual to corporate headquarters but employees must be located at a U.S. based Lockheed Martin business unit work location. The salary for this position will be adjusted to reflect the salary band for the geographic location of the selected employee. This position requires up to 75% travel.

A requirement for this position is having a TS/SCI security clearance. Expectations for work performed will include auditing the program finance function for LM programs audited and performing assist audit work for E&Y and year end on LM special access programs.

This position is assigned responsibilities involving evaluating and analyzing criminal intelligence information, suspicious activity reports and open source information to aid in investigations and identify criminal trends and identify potential threats. The Criminal Intelligence Analyst is an unclassified grant funded position through the Oklahoma Office of Homeland Security that is charged with bringing data-focused analysis skills and leadership to the Oklahoma Highway Patrol and the state Fusion Center, as well as, partnering with senior law enforcement management in the successful implementation of the Oklahoma Information Fusion Center. The Criminal Intelligence Analyst will help envision and articulate the needs of Intelligence and senior management customers, will communicate and implement the federal guidelines and requirements, and will guide and approve project deliverables. The Analyst will coordinate and collaborate with outside criminal justice agencies at the federal, state and local level. Prepare and present intelligence reports and assessments to senior management and other fusion center stakeholders.

TYPICAL FUNCTIONS:
The functions of this position may include the following:
Conducts technical analysis and evaluations of intelligence data or criminal activity.
Review, select, evaluate, and consolidate incoming intelligence data and related information and insures that follow-up actions are initiated; collects additional data to fill gaps; disseminates action items to the responsible enforcement entities.
Prepares or requests the preparation of descriptive intelligence reports, utilizing detailed charts and diagrams.
Makes inquiries about intelligence information received by telephone, email and teletype; reviews, analyzes and evaluates intelligence relating to criminal activity.
Interacts with representatives of other law enforcement agencies to exchange information regarding criminals and crimes, utilizing personal contacts, telephone, teletype or other media.
Maintains cross reference files of criminal and case information.
Prepares section activity reports for the chief analyst.
Liaison with private sector agencies and employees to facilitate the exchange of information.

QUALIFICATIONS:
Bachelors degree in Criminal Justice, Public Administration or a related field; or an equivalent substitution of experience with a government law enforcement or military agency performing technical tasks such as: research, reviewing written documentation to identify and extract relevant information, typing investigative reports, court documents or statistical data; using computer systems to acquire and organize information, operating teletype and computer systems to obtain information through OLETS, NLETS or NCIC or other criminal records or intelligence systems; analyzing information for relevance to a specific task.
Prior experience in crime or intelligence analysis, geographic profiling, compiling analytical reports, the use of statistical analysis.

Must be familiar with Windows 7 operating system, Microsoft Office 2010, and be able to speak and hear clearly through a telephone line.
Must be able to operate computer, printer, fax machine, copier, and telephone.
Must be able to pass a DPS background and polygraph, as well as a Federal secret level clearance.
Must be able to handle sensitive information and intelligence.

Medidata is making a real difference in the lives of patients everywhere by accelerating critical drug and medical device development, enabling life-saving drugs and medical devices to get to market faster. Our products sit at the convergence of the Technology and Life Sciences industries, one of most exciting areas for global innovation.

We invented the Medidata Clinical Cloud which is the primary technology solution powering clinical trials for over 90% of the world's top global pharmaceutical and medical-device companies - from study design and planning through execution, management and reporting. We are publicly traded (MDSO), have 850 customers with retention rates at 100% and a revenue run-rate of over $500M in 2017. Our customers include global pharmaceutical companies, biotech, diagnostic and device firms, leading academic medical centers, technical partners and contract research organizations.

Medidatas solutions have powered over 12,000 clinical trials to date giving us the largest collection of clinical trial data in the world. With this asset, we pioneer innovative, advanced applications and intelligent data analytics, bringing an unmatched level of quality and efficiency to clinical trials enabling treatments to reach waiting patients sooner.

We know that diverse teams win and therefore we are committed to selecting leaders and employees that represent the markets in which we operate. We are still led by our Co-founders, Tarek Sherif and Glen de Vries, and have global operations in US, Europe and Asia with 1600 employees.

Big Data analytics is not just about managing more or diverse data. Rather, it is about asking new questions, formulating new hypotheses, exploration and discovery, and making data-driven decisions. The Big Data function is responsible for analytics infrastructure in the cloud by leveraging open source technologies like Hadoop, Hive, Pig and more. Multidisciplinary work supporting reporting services, analytics pipelines and data warehouses
Performance analysis and capacity planning for our growing clusters
Mentor junior level team members

Love to solve complex problems and provide simple elegant reliable solutions. Have a passion for developing efficient, testable, and well-documented code

Experience interacting with security subsystems, includin oAuth and LDAP
Pride yourself as professional Java developer and an expert in the OO programming paradigm

Design and implementation of APIs and services to expose the data and abstract the tools
Relational Databases and persistence layers
Unit testing (JUnit, Mockito, PowerMock) and documentation (Javadoc)
Linux experience

Excellent communication skills

Positions in this function are responsible for the management and manipulation of mostly structured data, with a focus on building business intelligence tools, conducting analysis to distinguish patterns and recognize trends, performing normalization operations and assuring data quality. Depending on the specific role and business line, example responsibilities in this function could include creating specifications to bring data into a common structure, creating product specifications and models, developing data solutions to support analyses, performing analysis, interpreting results, developing actionable insights and presenting recommendations for use across the company. Roles in this function could partner with stakeholders to understand data requirements and develop tools and models such as segmentation, dashboards, data visualizations, decision aids and business case analysis to support the organization. Other roles involved could include producing and managing the delivery of activity and value analytics to external stakeholders and clients. Team members will typically use business intelligence, data visualization, query, analytic and statistical software to build solutions, perform analysis and interpret data. Positions in this function work on predominately descriptive and regression-based analytics and tend to leverage subject matter expert views in the design of their analytics and algorithms. This function is not intended for employees performing the following work: production of standard or self-service operational reporting, casual inference led (healthcare analytics) or data pattern recognition (data science) analysis; and/or image or unstructured data analysis using sophisticated theoretical frameworks.

Map client local terminologies to Optum One standard concepts
Work closely with clinical informatics specialists in domains such as lab and medication data
Writing specifications for engineers regarding how to process data
Work closely with engineering and operations teams as the client is implemented, to answer questions and resolve data issues that arise
Be responsible for monthly review of client data and dictionary updates and implementing appropriate revisions to Optum Analytics mapping tables
Investigate data anomalies to determine root cause, specify appropriate changes and work with engineering and operations teams as the change is implemented and tested
Research client questions on data results by identifying underlying data elements leveraged and providing descriptions of data transformations involved
Contribute to technical documentation of specifications and processes
Participate in the ongoing invention, testing and use of tools used by the team to improve processes and bring scale

job_title: Data Science Analyst - Business Technology Solutions
summary:
Job Description Summary
The Business Technology Solutions (BTS) Data Science Analyst is a member of a highly-motivated BTS team responsible for partnering with multiple IT and business divisions to evaluate, understand and deliver solutions for complex business problems. The team works as the strategic interface with assigned business divisions for the purpose of business-IT strategy development, solutions delivery, service management, risk management and relationship management. The BTS team provides highly-valued strategic consulting level support and guidance throughout key business technology initiatives.
The BTS Data Science Analyst incorporates the latest developments in Data Science (statistical modeling, machine learning, simulation and advanced visualization) to solve complex business problems. The Data Science Analyst will be able to identify a methodology to answer a business question, gather relevant data from multiple sources and evaluate its quality, perform exploratory data analysis and visualization, applied statistical methods to reach a reproducible answer, and present results that are usable in the context of CAAs business. The Data Science Analyst also assists in testing and developing the technology infrastructure to turn Data Science experiments into usable products.
The position will report to the assigned divisional BTS Manager or Lead.
Responsibilities
Data Wrangling:
Identify data sources that can be useful to answer business questions
Determine the optimal way to ingest this data into CAAs available technology platforms
Perform experiments on ingested data to evaluate quality and integrity
Build a data pipeline for ongoing data extraction
Provide input to data engineers for building ongoing external and internal data ETL pipelines
Data Exploration and Visualization:
Use advanced visualization techniques to present data insights in a compelling way
Apply advanced analytics to create metrics and KPIs that summarize insights from data
Determine the right choice between Business Intelligence tools and/or open-source visualization tools based on business and technical requirements.
Data Analysis:
Apply advanced statistical methods for classification and prediction, including machine learning methods
Document processes and analyses, using reproducible methods and scripts
Provide advice to the business on strengths and limitations of statistical results, to avoid misuse
Requirements gathering and Presentation of Results:
Elicit, analyze, and document business requirements, from user groups and project stakeholders.
Create and manage backlog of items by documenting business requirements and translating into technical specifications for solution implementation.
Manage requirements prioritization, implementation estimation and dependencies; traceability from business capability to test case.
Summarize results in business-friendly formats, and provide alternative levels of detail depending on business audiences
Anticipate questions from business partners and share data insights on an ongoing basis.
Required Capabilities
Minimum 3 years working in a Data Science/Business Analytics role with significant client exposure.
Bachelors degree or equivalent in a Mathematics or Science field, Computer Science of Business Management fields preferred.
Experience successfully implementing analytical solutions with real-world business impact.
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.
Exceptional oral and written communications skills.
Demonstrate initiative and ownership of tasks and projects.
Ability to prioritize, coordinate and complete tasks to meet deadlines.
Ability to work effectively both independently and in team environments.
Ability to present complex problems in simple terms with great presentation skills.
Experience extracting insights from data.
Proficiency using R, Python, Stata, SAS, Matlab or similar mathematical programming languages for advanced predictive modeling and visualization.
Experience using BI platfoms such as PowerBI, Tableau or Qlik.
Experience with Simulation modeling (System Dynamics, Agent-Based Simulation or Discrete Event Simulation) preferred.
Experience with Deep Learning methods and applications (Keras, Torch, TensorFlow, Theano, or others) preferred.
Experience with Natural Language Processing methods and applications preferred.
Experience with Excel and PowerPoint.
Environment
CAA has a service oriented collaborative environment where we help our colleagues then focus on our own work. Our standards for dress are professional i.e. suit & tie for men and appropriate professional clothes for women.

At Relay, we believe that data-driven decision-making is essential to helping our institution meet its goals. Researchers at Relay are committed to producing innovative and timely scholarship on how teachers and school leaders, in partnership with their schools and communities, can raise student achievement and help young people develop the character strengths that are needed to be successful in school and life.

Reporting to the Director of Research and Data, the Data Analyst will help to organize data across Relay to help program staff and senior leaders to make decisions. The Data Analyst will help to collect and manage the data as well as produce data visualizations and reports using data. Relay continues to extend its reach nationally and the Data Analyst will play a pivotal role in data reporting from all of Relay's programs and campuses.

As such, the Data Analyst will play a role in supporting teams in accessing data and using data for continuous learning and improvement efforts. This is an outstanding opportunity to make meaningful and foundational contributions to the work of an institution that is reshaping the landscape of urban, public education.

ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES

Collaborate on the design, management, and administration of internal data collection systems
Review, clean, and analyze Relay data to generate insight about institutional effectiveness and program quality and success (e.g., student performance, student satisfaction, student retention and persistence)
Perform data analysis to identify trends, anomalies, and potentially useful information for instructional faculty and senior staff (e.g., student performance, student satisfaction, student retention and persistence)
Produce various reports accurately and on time
Create and populate key dashboards using institutional data accurately and on time
Prepare visual representations of data and analytical results (e.g., tables, figures, presentation slides)
Communicate research findings to non-technical audiences, in writing, and verbally
Respond to requests for data from senior Relay staff on demand
QUALIFICATIONS

First and foremost, the Data Analyst must share the teams sense of urgency about the need to improve student achievement through phenomenal teacher and instructional leader preparation.

Additionally, candidates for the position must have the following:

BA/BS degree in education, mathematics, economics, public policy or the social sciences required; Masters degree preferred
Experience collecting, analyzing, and reporting data, associated with education
Demonstrated knowledge with various computer information and data management systems (i.e., Microsoft Excel), in addition to general proficiency and problem solving regarding information; experience using Stata preferred
Experience producing data visualizations and reports using complex datasets, especially using the software Tableau
Exceptional project management skills, attention to detail, and ability to multi-task
Excellent writing and communication skills
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Strong interpersonal skills and the ability to work effectively with a wide range of constituencies in a diverse community
Ability to work in a highly collaborative team environment while demonstrating the ability to solve problems independently
Ability to set priorities for use of ones time, work under pressure, and adjust tasks appropriately
A demonstrated passion for urban education and closing the opportunity gap
Ability to work efficiently, intensely, and within an entrepreneurial environment
Authorized to work in the United States
COMPENSATION

Relay offers a competitive salary and benefits package for full-time employees.

Work Shift:
1st shift (United States of America) Please review the following job description: Primary Purpose:
Assemble and prepare data for analysis and then use statistical and reporting techniques to summarize the data into actionable results for management. The data processing, statistical analysis, and reporting will be performed using SAS tools. It will be challenged to develop insights and interpretations related to the data and its summarization. This is a mid-level position under immediate supervision of a Senior Analytics Team Leader in the Corporate Credit Risk Management Department.
Essential Duties and Responsibilities:
Following is a summary of the essential functions for this job. Other duties may be performed, both major and minor, which are not mentioned below. Specific activities may change from time to time.
1. Support management and process owners in the collection and analysis of factual and dimensional data.
2. Assist with data definitions and planning for data marts.
3. Assist with defining and developing data sources, mapping data from source to target, and defining and developing required data transformations through translating business needs into technical solutions using Business Intelligence Tools (SAS, SQL, ETL, and OLAP).
4. Manage the validation of the data extracts and loads for data accuracy and completeness.
5. Implement data models and database designs, data access and table maintenance codes.
6. Understand requirements of data stewardship for datasets and data marts (fields, data values, etc.).
7. Work with Corporate Credit Risk Managers and process owners to identify business reporting requirements and prepare, execute and distribute reports/information.

job_title: Sr. Data Governance / Data Quality Architect
summary:
Data is critical to the success of any Data Driven Organization, and at Delta Air Lines, it is the lifeblood that drives value by providing the information to make strategic business decisions and process improvements. The Enterprise Information Management (EIM) Data Governance Architect (DGA) is responsible for working with the EIM Delivery and Development teams to develop data governance, data standardization and data design strategies. This person you will help establish, own and grow our client's practices around data intake, quality control, master data management, compliance, access and long-term growth of their integrations and reporting capabilities. Focusing on their enterprise systems and integrations, this role will provide leadership and horsepower when it comes to keeping their internal data accurate, safe and compliant. The total data landscapes involve 100's of Terabytes of active data with daily ingestion of terabytes across. Additionally, this individual will be involved with shaping and implementing an Enterprise Data Catalog.

DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES:
Lead, manage and grow the Data Governance practice for our enterprise
Document, assess, influence and synthesize business requirements to develop, enable and advance data governance and stewardship capabilities
Design and own future state concept of operations through the development of business process models and data flow diagrams
Lead Data Governance efforts start-to-finish, providing both project management and product leadership guidance
Facilitate and promote usage and adoption of the data governance tools, particularly among business users
Maintain and promote key data governance deliverables/assets, including data policies, data standards and data management roles and decision frameworks
Work with Business partners to recommend data control placements and control sets
Work closely with Data Analyst, Business Architects and Data Governance to achieve DQ objectives
Collaborate with the Data Delivery technology teams and architects to define and develop DQ solutions
Interact with business and technical peers in the evaluation of emerging industry trends and technologies relevant to data management
Assist in the establishment of a community of practice - a virtual organization that meets regularly to share ideas and best practices and promote a culture where data is managed as an asset of the company
Research and experiment with emerging Data Quality Profiling technologies and tools associated to data quality, metadata, data governance
Hands-on role in defining and designing of controls and visualizations
Develop Key Performance Indicators and dashboards to measure the success of the data governance program

EXPERIENCE/EDUCATION QUALIFICATIONS:
Bachelor's Degree
5-7 years' experience with data governance, data quality and standardization
An experienced Business Architect: as a result of your 5-7 years of experience, you have high empathy for business process issues arising from poor data quality, lack of controls and lack of proper oversight, and can lead discussions through critical-thinking problems toward resolution
A data pro: While you might not be able to whip up a fully-integrated data warehouse from scratch, you would be able to digest one and track along with data architects, modelers and developers, and have a solid understanding of end-to-end processes of data throughout the enterprise
A self-starter: with little guidance, you are able to get into the weeds with multiple teams at a time, continually searching for answers in all the lovely but rapid chaos
A practitioner: you seek to create a practice around Data Governance, one that will keep a long-term view in mind while being flexible to enhance and adjust along the way
A solid communicator: you can bring clarity to the complex world of data, integrations and compliance rules across teams including leadership, engineering, legal, security and process owners
A data diplomat: you can effectively push multiple teams to a common set of data definitions using your strengths in communication, negotiation, education and overall governance knowledge
In-depth knowledge of the following concepts: Master Data Management, Business Intelligence, Services Oriented Architecture, Enterprise Content Management.
Ability to think in the abstract, with the ability to understand multiple facets of complex technologies.
Experience in an application domain with an architectural understanding
Hands on Data profiling, data extraction, validations and remediation's tools.
Experience with Data Lake and data frameworks like Hadoop
Designed DQ Visualization & Dashboards and Data Steward UXs
Facilitated design sessions and user experiences walk through
Running Data Quality Assessments and reviewing results with Business and Tech teams and providing control recommendations.
Understanding of Enterprise Architecture processes for technology portfolio management and project governance, including technology selections and peer review.

HIGHLY PREFERRED SKILLS:
Experience with Data Governance/Standardization tools
Experience using Data Modeling tools, such as ERwin
Good knowledge of Data Lineage utilizing Data Cataloging toolsets
Good Knowledge of at least one Data Quality tool (Quality Stage, Informatica IDQ, Trillium)
Knowledge of ETL & BI tools (Informatica, Data stage, TIBCO, MuleSoft)
Knowledge of web services and/or Enterprise Application Integration
Teradata, Aster, Hadoop, UNIX and SQL
